Title : Southwood Open Space
Text : [[File:Southwood Open Space 5.JPG|thumb]]
'''Southwood Open Space''' is a 12.9 hectare [[Local Nature Reserve]] (LNR) in [[Old Malden]] in the [[Royal Borough of Kingston upon Thames]] in London. It is a linear park along the [[Hogsmill River]] between the Kingston Bypass opposite Elmbridge Avenue and the junction between the Hogsmill and a footpath to Manor Drive North.<ref name=LNR>{{cite web|url= http://www.lnr.naturalengland.org.uk/Special/lnr/lnr_details.asp?C=0&N=southwood&ID=1523|title= Southwood Open Space|series=Local Nature Reserves|publisher=Natural England| date =  |accessdate= 3 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://magic.defra.gov.uk/MagicMap.aspx?startTopic=Designations&activelayer=lnrIndex&query=REF_CODE%3D%271009641%27|title=Map of Southwood Open Space|series=Local Nature Reserves|publisher=Natural England| accessdate= 3 May 2014}}</ref>

The name Southwood Open Space is only used on the [[Natural England]] database of LNRs, and it is more commonly regarded as part of the Hogsmill River Park<ref name=LGO>{{cite web|url=http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=KIN022|title=Hogsmill River Park|publisher=London Parks and Gardens Trust|accessdate= 3 May 2014}}</ref> or Hogsmill Valley, which extends north to [[Elmbridge Open Space]] LNR. Hogsmill Valley is designated a [[Site of Nature Conservation Interest|Site of Borough Importance for Nature Conservation]], Grade 1.<ref name=GIGL>{{cite web|url=http://www.gigl.org.uk/online/site-Details.aspx?sID=KiBI02&sType=sinc|title=Hogsmill Valley|publisher=Greenspace Information for Greater London|year=2013|accessdate= 3 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gigl.org.uk/online/|title=iGiGL data portal (map)|publisher=Greenspace Information for Greater London|accessdate= 3 May 2014}}</ref>
 
The site is mainly grassland, with hedgerows of elm scrub. These were mainly dominated by elm trees until they were destroyed by [[Dutch Elm Disease]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surreycc.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0010/167824/TDLroute.pdf|title=Thames Down Link|publisher=Surrey County Council|page=1|accessdate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525143357/http://www.surreycc.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0010/167824/TDLroute.pdf|archivedate=25 May 2013|df=}}</ref>

The [[London Loop]] long distance walk goes through the park.

